    {
      "segment_id": "seg_225",
      "page_number": 22,
      "section": "chronicle_entry",
      "speaker": "pixel",
      "speaker_mode": "internal_monologue",
      "text": "We found a dying Keeper in the Shattered Span today. We fought people who wanted to destroy it. We lost. It died anyway, but not before showing us something no one was supposed to see: the Dimming wasn't natural. Someone—something—chose to put the Pillars to sleep. Chose to let the lights go out.",
      "direction": "Personal reflection on events",
      "audio_cues": {
        "tone": "weary honesty, major revelation",
        "pacing": "steady, measured",
        "emphasis_words": [
          "dying Keeper",
          "lost",
          "Dimming wasn't natural",
          "chose to let the lights go out"
        ]
      },
      "timing": {
        "pause_before_ms": 300,
        "pause_after_ms": 500,
        "estimated_duration_ms": 7200
      }
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "seg_226",
      "page_number": 22,
      "section": "chronicle_entry",
      "speaker": "pixel",
      "speaker_mode": "internal_monologue",
      "text": "The Quiet calls that knowledge poison. Maybe they're right. Maybe some truths do more harm than good. Maybe waking the Keepers will accelerate the end.",
      "direction": "Acknowledging the opposition's perspective",
      "audio_cues": {
        "tone": "doubtful reflection",
        "pacing": "slower, uncertainty",
        "emphasis_words": [
          "poison",
          "truths",
          "harm",
          "accelerate the end"
        ]
      },
      "timing": {
        "pause_before_ms": 400,
        "pause_after_ms": 500,
        "estimated_duration_ms": 4800
      }
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "seg_227",
      "page_number": 22,
      "section": "chronicle_entry",
      "speaker": "pixel",
      "speaker_mode": "internal_monologue",
      "text": "But here's what I know: that Keeper spent its dying breath trying to tell us one word. Trying to give us one piece of the puzzle. Even at the end, even broken and alone in a place where reality itself had shattered, it chose to remember. Chose to share.",
      "direction": "Pixel's conviction emerging",
      "audio_cues": {
        "tone": "building conviction",
        "pacing": "steady, growing stronger",
        "emphasis_words": [
          "dying breath",
          "one word",
          "chose to remember",
          "chose to share"
        ]
      },
      "timing": {
        "pause_before_ms": 400,
        "pause_after_ms": 500,
        "estimated_duration_ms": 6400
      }
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "seg_228",
      "page_number": 22,
      "section": "chronicle_entry",
      "speaker": "pixel",
      "speaker_mode": "internal_monologue",
      "text": "That's not poison. That's hope in its rawest form.",
      "direction": "Declaration of belief",
      "audio_cues": {
        "tone": "resolute belief",
        "pacing": "quick, final",
        "emphasis_words": [
          "poison",
          "hope",
          "rawest form"
        ]
      },
      "timing": {
        "pause_before_ms": 300,
        "pause_after_ms": 600,
        "estimated_duration_ms": 2400
      }
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "seg_229",
      "page_number": 22,
      "section": "chronicle_entry",
      "speaker": "pixel",
      "speaker_mode": "internal_monologue",
      "text": "Arc is questioning everything he thought he knew about himself. Clive is carrying memories that hurt to touch. Mochi absorbed something from that Keeper—fragments, impressions, something it can't express but can't forget. And The Quiet knows we're coming for more answers.",
      "direction": "Reflecting on team status",
      "audio_cues": {
        "tone": "observation of impact",
        "pacing": "steady, concerned",
        "emphasis_words": [
          "Arc",
          "questioning",
          "Clive",
          "memories that hurt",
          "Mochi",
          "The Quiet knows"
        ]
      },
      "timing": {
        "pause_before_ms": 400,
        "pause_after_ms": 500,
        "estimated_duration_ms": 6000
      }
    },
    {
      "segment_id": "seg_230",
      "page_number": 22,
      "section": "chronicle_entry",
      "speaker": "pixel",
      "speaker_mode": "internal_monologue",
      "text": "The lights are going out. Someone chose to dim them. And somewhere in the spaces between memory and Signal and ancient purpose, there's a truth waiting to be found.",
      "direction": "Identifying the central mystery",
      "audio_cues": {
        "tone": "mysterious, building",
        "pacing": "measured, building tension",
        "emphasis_words": [
          "lights are going out",
          "dim them",
          "truth"
        ]
